</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3366524752FFFB3FF45B696FAB7B115" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B9336AF752FFFB3FF45B696FAB7B115" blockId="6.[192,1440,1507,1627]" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">
<emphasis id="B958EABD752FFFB3FF45B696FEBCB2B5" bold="true" box="[192,337,1507,1531]" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C2C4D2C752FFFB3FED2B696FDBEB2B5" authority="Galileo &amp; Martins, 2010" authorityName="Galileo &amp; Martins" authorityYear="2010" box="[343,595,1507,1531]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Tropidion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argentina" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B958EABD752FFFB3FED2B696FDBEB2B5" box="[343,595,1507,1531]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">Tropidion argentina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A26B57C6752FFFB3FDDCB691FD55B2B5" box="[601,696,1508,1531]" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C4D2C752FFFB3FCDCB691FB0CB2B5" authority="(Martins, 1962)" baseAuthorityName="Martins" baseAuthorityYear="1962" box="[857,1249,1507,1531]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Tropidion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="intermedium">
<emphasis id="B958EABD752FFFB3FCDCB691FBC7B2B5" box="[857,1066,1507,1531]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">T. intermedium (</emphasis>
Martins, 1962)
</taxonomicName>
concerning unarmed elytral apices, but it is distinguished by its general reddish-brown coloring, having a yellow spot on the elytra, and by the pronotum, which presents three tubercles. On 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C4D2C752FFFB3FBA7B551FB08B175" baseAuthorityName="Martins" baseAuthorityYear="1962" box="[1058,1253,1571,1595]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Tropidion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="intermedium">
<emphasis id="B958EABD752FFFB3FBA7B551FB08B175" box="[1058,1253,1571,1595]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">T. intermedium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the elytra are yellowish and without spots, the appendices are reddish and the pronotum presents five tubercles.
</paragraph>
